{{Quote|If the information in my databanks are accurate, during the last decades of the Old Republic podraces were run on this track. The series was formed and controlled by the Hutts many years ago. Following the decline of podracing's popularity, this track was more or less abandoned by the Hutts. It was eventually taken over by a small band of swoop racers, who used it to stage a regular series of semi-legitimate races.|The race coordinator, to a spacer|<ref name="SWG">{{GalaxiesAED}}</ref>}}
[[File:Mos_Espa_Race.jpg|thumb|Swoop gangs making use of the Mos Espa Circuit]]
The '''Mos Espa Circuit''', also known as the '''Mos Espa Raceway''' or the '''Mos Espa Podrace circuit''', and later the '''Old Mos Espa Arena Circuit''',<ref name="Ghost">''[[Tatooine Ghost]]''</ref> was a [[Podracing/Legends|podracing]] and later [[Swoop/Legends|swoop]]-racing track located on the desert [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] close to [[Mos Entha/Legends|Mos Entha]].

Mos Espa Ciruit was where the [[Boonta Eve Classic/Legends|Boonta Eve Classic]] podrace was held [[Standard year/Legends|annually]].<ref name="Mos Espa Circuit CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|334|Mos Espa Circuit}}</ref> Following the decline of podracing popularity with the departure of public spectacle and [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba Desilijic Tiure]], the most powerful of the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] gangsters on Tatooine, moved from the [[Spaceport/Legends|port]] [[City/Legends|city]] of [[Mos Espa/Legends|Mos Espa]] in favor of the growing city of [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]], the course was left largely abandoned.<ref name="Mos Espa CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|334|Mos Espa}}</ref> During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], the local [[Swoop gang/Legends|swoop gangs]] used this track for their own racing events.<ref name="SWG" /> In [[8 ABY/Legends|8 ABY]], [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] test drove the [[Novastar Corporation|Novastar]] swoop at the circuit to find [[Kitster Chanchani Banai]], who had stolen a [[Killik Twilight|piece]] of [[Alderaanian/Legends|Alderaanian]] moss art.<ref name="Ghost" />

{{Loc-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Mos_Espa_Raceway.png|thumb|200px|The track in ''Racer Rush'']]
[[File:MosEspaCircuit.jpg|thumb|200px|The track in ''Star Wars Galaxies'']]
The film [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']] marks the first appearance of the Mos Espa Circuit.<ref name="TPM">{{Film|I}}</ref> The Circuit is depicted differently in various ''[[Star Wars]]'' media. Based on the course shown in the film, the [[2000]] reference book ''[[Inside the Worlds of Star Wars: Episode I]]'' provides a map of the Mos Espa Circuit,<ref name="Inside">''[[Inside the Worlds of Star Wars: Episode I]]''</ref> although the track featured in the ''[[Racer Rush]]'' [[Star Wars video games|video game]] is much more simplistic than the one displayed in ''The Phantom Menace'': it does not include the tunnel segment and it takes only up to 2 minutes to race through its one lap.<ref name="Racer Rush">{{SWArchive|url=play/online-games/racer-rush|text=Racer Rush|int=Racer Rush}}</ref> However, the [[:File:MosEspaCircuit.jpg|Mos Espa Circuit]] in the ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'' video game is in keeping with the layout from ''Inside the Worlds of Star Wars: Episode I''.<ref name="SWG" /><ref name="Inside" /> The Old Mos Espa Arena Circuit was added to ''Star Wars Galaxies'' with the "[[W:c:swg:Update Notes: 27 July 04|Publish 9.2]]," released on [[July 27]], [[2004]].<ref name="SonyCite-Publish 9: Secrets of the Force">{{SonyCite|url=recent_updates.jsp?o=62675|text=Publish 9: Secrets of the Force}}</ref>

